## Data Flow Patterns

### Publish-Subscribe (MQTT)
- ESP32 devices publish sensor data to MQTT topics
- Backend subscribes to device topics for real-time updates
- Frontend receives updates via WebSocket/Server-Sent Events

### Request-Response (REST API)
- Mobile app makes REST calls for CRUD operations
- Backend validates, processes, stores data
- Returns JSON responses with status codes

### Job Queue (Bull/Redis)
- Long-running tasks enqueued (AI analysis, bulk exports)
- Workers process tasks asynchronously
- Results stored and notified via WebSocket

### Broadcast (WebSocket)
- Server-to-client real-time updates
- Kitchen display updates
- Alert notifications
- Live analytics dashboard

